Package: spectrolab
Type: Package
Title: Class and methods for hyperspectral data
Version: 0.0.1
Author: as.person("Jose Eduardo Meireles <meireles@umn.edu> [aut, cre]"), 
    as.person("Anna K. Schweiger <anna.k.schweiger@gmail.com> [aut, cre]")
Maintainer: Anna K. Schweiger <anna.k.schweiger@gmail.com>
Description: I/O, processing and visualization of data from field spectrometers,
    including SVC, ASD and PSR (Spectral Evolution). Implements an S3 class
    `spectra` that other packages can build on. Provides methods to access, plot, 
    manipulate, splice sensor overlap, vector normalize and smooth spectra.
Depends:
    R (>= 3.3.2)
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
Suggests: knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    testthat
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Imports: prospectr,
    devtools,
    parallel
